    <div class="subsection">
      <h3>Operational Considerations</h3>
      <p>While the feature functions as designed, be aware of these operational considerations:</p>
      
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Configuration Permanence:</strong> Once you select a calculation base and salary components, changing them affects all active payroll transactions. Plan changes carefully.</li>
        <li><strong>Public Holiday Dependency:</strong> Accurate calculations depend on maintaining an up-to-date public holiday calendar. Missing or incorrect holidays will skew results.</li>
        <li><strong>Month-to-Month Variation:</strong> When using Calendar Days, expect natural variation in daily rates due to different month lengths.</li>
        <li><strong>Manual Intervention Required:</strong> <span class="citation" data-source="zendesk" data-ref="14243760419089">When payroll month is open and prorated salary transactions exist, super admin must manually reject and resave transactions</span> before configuration changes.</li>
        <li><strong>Jurisdiction-Specific:</strong> Ensure your configuration aligns with labor law requirements for your specific jurisdiction (UAE, KSA, etc.).</li>
      </ul>
